HEADWORD: Creamy
<hw>Cream"y</hw> <pr>(kr?m"?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Full of, or
containing, cream; resembling cream, in nature, appearance, or taste;
creamlike; unctuous.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Creamy</xex> bowls.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Collins.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧Lines of <xex>creamy</xex> spray.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Tennyson.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧Your <xex>creamy</xex> words but cozen.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Beau. & Fl.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

